  <prompt>Author a throwaway integration test that invokes `AnalysisOrchestrationService` (or `sprk_playbookconsumer` based on the task 001 decision document — even though task 030 hasn't rewritten the production wrapper yet, this smoke proves the playbook is dispatchable by directly invoking the orchestration service). Pass `BRIEF-NARRATE` as the playbook code along with a hand-crafted `DailyBriefingNarrateRequest` payload (synthesized fixture, no real user data). Verify: (a) no 500 response, (b) response shape conforms to expected playbook output, (c) the parallel GenerateChannelNarratives branches and ValidateEntityNames Tool executed. Capture a sample response in `notes/smoke/017-narrate-playbook-smoke.md`. The test is throwaway; do not check it into the production test suite.</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. BFF + JPS integration tester — proves end-to-end dispatchability of newly deployed playbook before production wrapper rewrite in PR 4.</role>

  <goal>One captured sample response from a real invocation of `BRIEF-NARRATE` via the orchestration service against spaarkedev1 (or local BFF pointed at spaarkedev1). Response demonstrates that the playbook is dispatchable + the node graph executes end-to-end. Sample recorded in `notes/smoke/017-narrate-playbook-smoke.md`.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>R4 spec FR-4 AC-4b (line 125-126) requires "BFF wrapper endpoint successfully dispatches narrate request to this playbook; receives valid response". The full production wrapper rewrite happens in task 030 (PR 4). This smoke is intermediate evidence — proves the PR 2 data deployment (playbook row + Action rows) is dispatchable before PR 3/PR 4 invest further. CLAUDE.md decisions log notes "the dispatch path was decided in task 001"; this smoke validates that decision empirically.</background>
